reviewText:
I recommend it for people who like a good platformer game with an awesome soundtrack.
Completed it in my first playthrough, wish it was longer, got ~50% of the acheivements, plan on getting them all.
Recommend playing it with a controller, you don't need an expensive and fancy one, a D-pad and 4 buttons is all you need.

Pros:
+ Nice and inovating platforming mechanics;
+ Killer music;
+ Delightful pixel graphics;
+ Cheap;
+ You can replay it and it doesn't get boring because there's a lot of acheivements;
+ A good challenge. (some people like their games hard-ish)

Cons:
- A good challenge; (some people like their games easy)
- Too short;
- Spaceship segments feel kinda out-of-place.
- Way too short.

I'd like to congratulate the developers for making such a nice game, and I hope they come out with a sequel for this, cause Grigori is still Out There Somewhere"."

